# TypeScript Sync Tooling

## Runtime

- Require Node.js 22.18+.
- Run TypeScript source directly with Node type stripping.
- Use erasable TypeScript syntax only: no enums, namespaces, or parameter
  properties.
- Use `.ts` extensions in relative ESM imports.

## Structure

- Entry points: `src/cli/*.ts`.
- Shared logic: `src/lib/*.ts`.
- Shared sync types: `src/types/*.ts`.
- Config defaults: `config/sync.json`; scripts read config and do not write it.

## Git Replay

- Use the `git` CLI only.
- Preserve upstream author metadata in `GIT_AUTHOR_*`.
- Preserve upstream committer metadata in `GIT_COMMITTER_*`.
- Message body is LF only and follows the template in `docs/PLAN.md`.
- On failure mid-batch, stop without pushing and keep the checkpoint.
- First replayed commit parent is `config/sync.json` -> `Destination.BaseCommit`.
- Bootstrap when any sync branch is missing; `--clean` resets sync branches first.

## Logging

- Print progress with `[sync]`, `[sync][warn]`, and `[sync][error]`.
- Exit non-zero on failure; exit zero when there is nothing to do or sync
  succeeds.

## External Tools

- Required: `git`.
- Optional in CI: `gh` for upstream SHA checks.
